<div id="Idea_3932"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3932-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3932">Higher Salary, Lower COLA for Government Employees&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/8414-4049">eklahn</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">2 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Look...a person making $20,000/yr, getting a 3% COLA, gets $600 (whoopee).  A person making $100,000/yr, getting the same 3% COLA, gets $3000. Unfair.  Consider decreasing COLA percentage as salary increases.</div>
